review_blob: One of my favorites. Perfectly balanced. The hops are present but not overpowering. Citrus is apparent in the flavor. Grapefruit possibly. Drinkable for an IPA. Smells mostly hoppy with some fruity hints. Pours a hazy gold color. Great beer.

All around good beer. Very drinkable. Smells and tastes earthy with the malt taste overpowering the hops a bit. Beautiful amber color. Great scent and appearance when poured into proper lager glassware.

Had on tap at Fat Heads in Pittsburgh under the moniker Fat Heads Ale.  Pours copper color with a thick white head. Smells hoppy with slight maltiness. Tastes slightly hoppy with a caramel and malty accents. Perfect amount of carbonation. Easily my favorite bitter.

Bottle. Pours a hazy gold color with a white head. Smells of orange and wheat. Complex taste consisting of several spices. You can get orange peel, wheat and coriander right away. Best enjoyed with salads. Very good belgian white.

On tap. Pours a slightly dark amber color with an off white head. Smells mainly of vanilla. Tastes sweet like graham, vanilla, and some caramel. Very pleased overall. I ,like many, was stunned to find out this was an A-B product.
Macro pale lager. Very drinkable. Slightly more flavorful and enjoyable than other american macros.
Very typical macro light lager. Highly carbonated. Tastes faintly of pale malts. Slightly better than others though.
Bottle. Poured clear gold. I was slightly surprised as this tastes better than a macro with artificial honey flavors. Slightly malty. Decent mouthfeel. Pretty average overall.
Bottle. Pours dark brown. One of the least flavorful porters Ive tasted. Some chocolate, some malt, no hops. Very thin mouthfeel for a porter.
Bottle. One of the better beers Labatt has to offer, which isnt saying too much, but not a bad beer. Very nice reddish brown color with a typical bitter red lager taste.
Bottle. Pours light gold. Flavor and aroma consist of hops and malt. Slightly metal tasting. Very bland beer.
Bottle. Pours light copper. Smell is very spicy, many things to take in here, cinnamon and nutmeg most prevalent. Flavor is dominated by cinnamon. Nice mouthfeel. Average winter warmer.
Pours light amber with a small white head. Slightly nutty taste, very drinkable. A good alternative to other macro lagers.
